Ed Miliband said there is 'nothing more British than the dream of home-ownership' He wants to scrap stamp duty for most first-time buyers and give local people priority for new homes . 
  Labour also wants to ban developers hoarding land which could be built on . 
  The policies triggered a drop in the value of shares of construction firms . 
  Barrett Developments and Taylor Wimpey saw shares fall . 
  Mr Miliband said he would introduce rent controls and curbing rent rises . 
  He said he wants to prioritise new homes for local people in a speech in Stockton . 
 